{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/use-the-brute-force-learning-technique-to-gain-new-skills-38a06dc23768", "time": 1683014697.07183, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/use-the-brute-force-learning-technique-to-gain-new-skills-38a06dc23768/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Use the brute-force learning technique to gain new skills | by Dimitris Poulopoulos | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Use the brute-force learning technique to gain new skills", "description": "Study new developments, stay up to date and conquer new knowledge with one simple trick."}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://mailchi.mp/d2d2d4a109b5/learning-rate-newsletter", "anchor_text": "Learning Rate", "paragraph_index": 3}, {"url": "https://mailchi.mp/d2d2d4a109b5/learning-rate-newsletter", "anchor_text": "here", "paragraph_index": 3}, {"url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/dpoulopoulos/", "anchor_text": "Dimitris Poulopoulos", "paragraph_index": 11}, {"url": "https://www.arrikto.com/", "anchor_text": "Arrikto", "paragraph_index": 11}, {"url": "https://medium.com/@dpoulopoulos", "anchor_text": "Medium", "paragraph_index": 12}, {"url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/dpoulopoulos/", "anchor_text": "LinkedIn", "paragraph_index": 12}, {"url": "https://twitter.com/james2pl", "anchor_text": "@james2pl", "paragraph_index": 12}, {"url": "http://www.dimpo.me", "anchor_text": "www.dimpo.me", "paragraph_index": 15}], "all_paragraphs": ["If you\u2019re just entering the workforce or trying to change career paths, learning new skills and developing new abilities will take you a long way and set you apart in the job market. But how can you efficiently gain and retain new knowledge?", "We are lucky to have access to more knowledge and information than any generation before. If you have the right question, the right answer is just a few clicks away. However, it\u2019s important to be open to educators who can approach our problem from different angles.", "There are several ways and countless methods to help you learn new things without going back to college; books, online courses, voluntary jobs, internships, etc. But in this story, I want to highlight a simple technique that helps me get ready: Brute-Force Learning. You can apply it to achieve anything you set your mind to, but my experience comes from the world of Information Technology and Digital Systems. Thus, that\u2019s where I draw my examples from.", "Learning Rate is a newsletter for those who are curious about the world of AI and MLOps. You\u2019ll hear from me every Friday with updates and thoughts on the latest AI news and articles. Subscribe here!", "Imagine that you are trying to learn a new programming language, a new platform like Kubernetes, or even a new concept, like Test-Driven Development (TDD). First, you try to understand the why; why is Kubernetes important? Why TDD helps you be a better software engineer? Why Python is a great new language to add to my toolbelt?", "Having the why in your pocket, you\u2019ll try to find an introductory book or video series to understand the basics: variables, control-flow and loops in Python, pods and services in Kubernetes, or how to mock services. But what Brute-Force Learning tells you is don\u2019t invest in one course; get two!", "In the beginning, find one great introductory course and dive in. Learn the theory, study the exercises and complete every section. Then, spot another beginner\u2019s course, that approaches the same subject from a different angle and do the same.", "But, what is in it for you? Isn\u2019t that a total waste of time? I would argue not. The first time you study a subject, everything is new. Your brain is bombarded with new terminology, rules and concepts. By the end of the course, you will have internalized a significant percentage of it, but not everything.", "Going over the whole thing again, but from a different perspective, will permit you to focus on the details and sand off the rough edges. The second time, not everything is new and the a-ha moments come more often. Moreover, the new angle will give you a novel point of view and keep you from doing another dull revision.", "After finishing the second course, you will feel more confident to dive into the more advanced sections and continue to brute-force your way to mastery.", "In this story, we saw what the Brute-Force Learning technique is and how it can help you study and master new concepts. We are lucky to have access to more knowledge and information than any generation before. If you have the right question, the correct answer is just a few clicks away. However, it\u2019s essential to be open to educators who can approach our problem from different angles.", "My name is Dimitris Poulopoulos and I\u2019m a machine learning engineer working for Arrikto. I have worked on designing and implementing AI and software solutions for major clients such as the European Commission, Eurostat, IMF, the European Central Bank, OECD, and IKEA.", "If you are interested in reading more posts about Machine Learning, Deep Learning, Data Science and DataOps follow me on Medium, LinkedIn or @james2pl on twitter.", "Opinions expressed are solely my own and do not express the views or opinions of my employer.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "Machine Learning Engineer. I talk about AI, MLOps, and Python programming. More about me: www.dimpo.me"], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2F38a06dc23768&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fuse-the-brute-force-learning-technique-to-gain-new-skills-38a06dc23768&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign